  "prompt": "What should I do if my PayPal account is hacked?",
  "response": "If your PayPal account is hacked, here are some steps to take:\n\n1. Immediate actions:\n- Change your PayPal password immediately\n- Enable two-factor authentication\n- Log out of all devices\n- Contact PayPal customer support\n- Report unauthorized transactions\n\n2. Financial protection:\n- Check recent transactions for any suspicious activity\n- Contact your bank/credit card company if needed\n- Request a chargeback for fraudulent transactions\n- Monitor your bank statements closely\n\n3. Security measures:\n- Link a new credit card or bank account\n- Check your account recovery email\n- Scan your computer for malware\n- Use a strong, unique password\n- Update passwords on other accounts\n\n4. Additional precautions:\n- Check your credit report\n- Consider placing a fraud alert\n- Use additional security tools like fraud monitoring\n\n5. Prevention for future:\n- Use strong, unique passwords\n- Enable two-factor authentication\n- Be cautious of phishing emails\n- Use secure networks\n- Regularly monitor account activity\n\nPayPal's specific contact information for account recovery and fraud:\n- Customer support: 1-888-221-1161\n- Resolution center: Available on PayPal website\n\nRemember to document everything and act quickly to minimize potential damage.",
